50         jQuery.Animation = function Animation(elem, properties, options) {
51     
52             var result,
53                 stopped,
54                 index = 0,
55                 length = animationPrefilters.length,
56                 deferred = jQuery.Deferred().always(function () {
57                     // don't match elem in the :animated selector
58                     delete tick.elem;
59                 }),
60                 tick = function () {
61                     if (stopped) {
62                         return false;
63                     }
64                     var currentTime = fxNow || createFxNow(),
65                         remaining = Math.max(0, animation.startTime + animation.duration - currentTime),
66                         // archaic crash bug won't allow us to use 1 - ( 0.5 || 0 ) (#12497)
67                         temp = remaining / animation.duration || 0,
68                         percent = 1 - temp,
69                         index = 0,
70                         length = animation.tweens.length;
71     
72                     for (; index < length ; index++) {
73                         animation.tweens[index].run(percent);
74                     }
75     
76                     deferred.notifyWith(elem, [animation, percent, remaining]);
77     
78                     if (percent < 1 && length) {
79                         return remaining;
80                     } else {
81                         deferred.resolveWith(elem, [animation]);
82                         return false;
83                     }
84                 },
85                 animation = deferred.promise({
86                     elem: elem,
87                     props: jQuery.extend({}, properties),
88                     opts: jQuery.extend(true, { specialEasing: {} }, options),
89                     originalProperties: properties,
90                     originalOptions: options,
91                     startTime: fxNow || createFxNow(),
92                     duration: options.duration,
93                     tweens: [],
94                     createTween: function (prop, end) {
95                         var tween = jQuery.Tween(elem, animation.opts, prop, end,
96                                 animation.opts.specialEasing[prop] || animation.opts.easing);
97                         animation.tweens.push(tween);
98                         return tween;
99                     },
100                     stop: function (gotoEnd) {
101                         var index = 0,
102                             // if we are going to the end, we want to run all the tweens
103                             // otherwise we skip this part
104                             length = gotoEnd ? animation.tweens.length : 0;
105                         if (stopped) {
106                             return this;
107                         }
108                         stopped = true;
109                         for (; index < length ; index++) {
110                             animation.tweens[index].run(1);
111                         }
112     
113                         // resolve when we played the last frame
114                         // otherwise, reject
115                         if (gotoEnd) {
116                             deferred.resolveWith(elem, [animation, gotoEnd]);
117                         } else {
118                             deferred.rejectWith(elem, [animation, gotoEnd]);
119                         }
120                         return this;
121                     }
122                 }),
123                 props = animation.props;
124     
125             propFilter(props, animation.opts.specialEasing);
126     
127             for (; index < length ; index++) {
128                 result = animationPrefilters[index].call(animation, elem, props, animation.opts);
129                 if (result) {
130                     return result;
131                 }
132             }
133     
134             createTweens(animation, props);
135     
136             if (jQuery.isFunction(animation.opts.start)) {
137                 animation.opts.start.call(elem, animation);
138             }
139     
140             jQuery.fx.timer(
141                 jQuery.extend(tick, {
142                     elem: elem,
143                     anim: animation,
144                     queue: animation.opts.queue
145                 })
146             );
147     
148             // attach callbacks from options
149             return animation.progress(animation.opts.progress)
150                 .done(animation.opts.done, animation.opts.complete)
151                 .fail(animation.opts.fail)
152                 .always(animation.opts.always);
153         };
154         jQuery.Callbacks = function (options) {
155             /// <summary>
156             ///     A multi-purpose callbacks list object that provides a powerful way to manage callback lists.
157             /// </summary>
158             /// <param name="options" type="String">
159             ///     An optional list of space-separated flags that change how the callback list behaves.
160             /// </param>
161             /// <returns type="Callbacks" />
162     
163     
164             // Convert options from String-formatted to Object-formatted if needed
165             // (we check in cache first)
166             options = typeof options === "string" ?
167                 (optionsCache[options] || createOptions(options)) :
168                 jQuery.extend({}, options);
169     
170             var // Last fire value (for non-forgettable lists)
171                 memory,
172                 // Flag to know if list was already fired
173                 fired,
174                 // Flag to know if list is currently firing
175                 firing,
176                 // First callback to fire (used internally by add and fireWith)
177                 firingStart,
178                 // End of the loop when firing
179                 firingLength,
180                 // Index of currently firing callback (modified by remove if needed)
181                 firingIndex,
182                 // Actual callback list
183                 list = [],
184                 // Stack of fire calls for repeatable lists
185                 stack = !options.once && [],
186                 // Fire callbacks
187                 fire = function (data) {
188                     memory = options.memory && data;
189                     fired = true;
190                     firingIndex = firingStart || 0;
191                     firingStart = 0;
192                     firingLength = list.length;
193                     firing = true;
194                     for (; list && firingIndex < firingLength; firingIndex++) {
195                         if (list[firingIndex].apply(data[0], data[1]) === false && options.stopOnFalse) {
196                             memory = false; // To prevent further calls using add
197                             break;
198                         }
199                     }
200                     firing = false;
201                     if (list) {
202                         if (stack) {
203                             if (stack.length) {
204                                 fire(stack.shift());
205                             }
206                         } else if (memory) {
207                             list = [];
208                         } else {
209                             self.disable();
210                         }
211                     }
212                 },
213                 // Actual Callbacks object
214                 self = {
215                     // Add a callback or a collection of callbacks to the list
216                     add: function () {
217                         if (list) {
218                             // First, we save the current length
219                             var start = list.length;
220                             (function add(args) {
221                                 jQuery.each(args, function (_, arg) {
222                                     var type = jQuery.type(arg);
223                                     if (type === "function") {
224                                         if (!options.unique || !self.has(arg)) {
225                                             list.push(arg);
226                                         }
227                                     } else if (arg && arg.length && type !== "string") {
228                                         // Inspect recursively
229                                         add(arg);
230                                     }
231                                 });
232                             })(arguments);
233                             // Do we need to add the callbacks to the
234                             // current firing batch?
235                             if (firing) {
236                                 firingLength = list.length;
237                                 // With memory, if we're not firing then
238                                 // we should call right away
239                             } else if (memory) {
240                                 firingStart = start;
241                                 fire(memory);
242                             }
243                         }
244                         return this;
245                     },
246                     // Remove a callback from the list
247                     remove: function () {
248                         if (list) {
249                             jQuery.each(arguments, function (_, arg) {
250                                 var index;
251                                 while ((index = jQuery.inArray(arg, list, index)) > -1) {
252                                     list.splice(index, 1);
253                                     // Handle firing indexes
254                                     if (firing) {
255                                         if (index <= firingLength) {
256                                             firingLength--;
257                                         }
258                                         if (index <= firingIndex) {
259                                             firingIndex--;
260                                         }
261                                     }
262                                 }
263                             });
264                         }
265                         return this;
266                     },
267                     // Check if a given callback is in the list.
268                     // If no argument is given, return whether or not list has callbacks attached.
269                     has: function (fn) {
270                         return fn ? jQuery.inArray(fn, list) > -1 : !!(list && list.length);
271                     },
272                     // Remove all callbacks from the list
273                     empty: function () {
274                         list = [];
275                         firingLength = 0;
276                         return this;
277                     },
278                     // Have the list do nothing anymore
279                     disable: function () {
280                         list = stack = memory = undefined;
281                         return this;
282                     },
283                     // Is it disabled?
284                     disabled: function () {
285                         return !list;
286                     },
287                     // Lock the list in its current state
288                     lock: function () {
289                         stack = undefined;
290                         if (!memory) {
291                             self.disable();
292                         }
293                         return this;
294                     },
295                     // Is it locked?
296                     locked: function () {
297                         return !stack;
298                     },
299                     // Call all callbacks with the given context and arguments
300                     fireWith: function (context, args) {
301                         args = args || [];
302                         args = [context, args.slice ? args.slice() : args];
303                         if (list && (!fired || stack)) {
304                             if (firing) {
305                                 stack.push(args);
306                             } else {
307                                 fire(args);
308                             }
309                         }
310                         return this;
311                     },
312                     // Call all the callbacks with the given arguments
313                     fire: function () {
314                         self.fireWith(this, arguments);
315                         return this;
316                     },
317                     // To know if the callbacks have already been called at least once
318                     fired: function () {
319                         return !!fired;
320                     }
321                 };
322     
323             return self;
324         };
325         jQuery.Deferred = function (func) {
326             /// <summary>
327             ///     A constructor function that returns a chainable utility object with methods to register multiple callbacks into callback queues, invoke callback queues, and relay the success or failure state of any synchronous or asynchronous function.
328             /// </summary>
329             /// <param name="func" type="Function">
330             ///     A function that is called just before the constructor returns.
331             /// </param>
332             /// <returns type="Deferred" />
333     
334             var tuples = [
335     				// action, add listener, listener list, final state
336     				["resolve", "done", jQuery.Callbacks("once memory"), "resolved"],
337     				["reject", "fail", jQuery.Callbacks("once memory"), "rejected"],
338     				["notify", "progress", jQuery.Callbacks("memory")]
339             ],
340     			state = "pending",
341     			promise = {
342     			    state: function () {
343     			        return state;
344     			    },
345     			    always: function () {
346     			        deferred.done(arguments).fail(arguments);
347     			        return this;
348     			    },
349     			    then: function ( /* fnDone, fnFail, fnProgress */) {
350     			        var fns = arguments;
351     			        return jQuery.Deferred(function (newDefer) {
352     			            jQuery.each(tuples, function (i, tuple) {
353     			                var action = tuple[0],
354     								fn = jQuery.isFunction(fns[i]) && fns[i];
355     			                // deferred[ done | fail | progress ] for forwarding actions to newDefer
356     			                deferred[tuple[1]](function () {
357     			                    var returned = fn && fn.apply(this, arguments);
358     			                    if (returned && jQuery.isFunction(returned.promise)) {
359     			                        returned.promise()
360     										.done(newDefer.resolve)
361     										.fail(newDefer.reject)
362     										.progress(newDefer.notify);
363     			                    } else {
364     			                        newDefer[action + "With"](this === promise ? newDefer.promise() : this, fn ? [returned] : arguments);
365     			                    }
366     			                });
367     			            });
368     			            fns = null;
369     			        }).promise();
370     			    },
371     			    // Get a promise for this deferred
372     			    // If obj is provided, the promise aspect is added to the object
373     			    promise: function (obj) {
374     			        return obj != null ? jQuery.extend(obj, promise) : promise;
375     			    }
376     			},
377     			deferred = {};
378     
379             // Keep pipe for back-compat
380             promise.pipe = promise.then;
381     
382             // Add list-specific methods
383             jQuery.each(tuples, function (i, tuple) {
384                 var list = tuple[2],
385     				stateString = tuple[3];
386     
387                 // promise[ done | fail | progress ] = list.add
388                 promise[tuple[1]] = list.add;
389     
390                 // Handle state
391                 if (stateString) {
392                     list.add(function () {
393                         // state = [ resolved | rejected ]
394                         state = stateString;
395     
396                         // [ reject_list | resolve_list ].disable; progress_list.lock
397                     }, tuples[i ^ 1][2].disable, tuples[2][2].lock);
398                 }
399     
400                 // deferred[ resolve | reject | notify ]
401                 deferred[tuple[0]] = function () {
402                     deferred[tuple[0] + "With"](this === deferred ? promise : this, arguments);
403                     return this;
404                 };
405                 deferred[tuple[0] + "With"] = list.fireWith;
406             });
407     
408             // Make the deferred a promise
409             promise.promise(deferred);
410     
411             // Call given func if any
412             if (func) {
413                 func.call(deferred, deferred);
414             }
415     
416             // All done!
417             return deferred;
418         };
419         jQuery.Event = function (src, props) {
420     
421             // Allow instantiation without the 'new' keyword
422             if (!(this instanceof jQuery.Event)) {
423                 return new jQuery.Event(src, props);
424             }
425     
426             // Event object
427             if (src && src.type) {
428                 this.originalEvent = src;
429                 this.type = src.type;
430     
431                 // Events bubbling up the document may have been marked as prevented
432                 // by a handler lower down the tree; reflect the correct value.
433                 this.isDefaultPrevented = (src.defaultPrevented ||
434                     src.getPreventDefault && src.getPreventDefault()) ? returnTrue : returnFalse;
435     
436                 // Event type
437             } else {
438                 this.type = src;
439             }
440     
441             // Put explicitly provided properties onto the event object
442             if (props) {
443                 jQuery.extend(this, props);
444             }
445     
446             // Create a timestamp if incoming event doesn't have one
447             this.timeStamp = src && src.timeStamp || jQuery.now();
448     
449             // Mark it as fixed
450             this[jQuery.expando] = true;

495         jQuery.access = function (elems, fn, key, value, chainable, emptyGet, raw) {
496     
497             var i = 0,
498     			length = elems.length,
499     			bulk = key == null;
500     
501             // Sets many values
502             if (jQuery.type(key) === "object") {
503                 chainable = true;
504                 for (i in key) {
505                     jQuery.access(elems, fn, i, key[i], true, emptyGet, raw);
506                 }
507     
508                 // Sets one value
509             } else if (value !== undefined) {
510                 chainable = true;
511     
512                 if (!jQuery.isFunction(value)) {
513                     raw = true;
514                 }
515     
516                 if (bulk) {
517                     // Bulk operations run against the entire set
518                     if (raw) {
519                         fn.call(elems, value);
520                         fn = null;
521     
522                         // ...except when executing function values
523                     } else {
524                         bulk = fn;
525                         fn = function (elem, key, value) {
526                             return bulk.call(jQuery(elem), value);
527                         };
528                     }
529                 }
530     
531                 if (fn) {
532                     for (; i < length; i++) {
533                         fn(elems[i], key, raw ? value : value.call(elems[i], i, fn(elems[i], key)));
534                     }
535                 }
536             }
537     
538             return chainable ?
539                 elems :
540     
541     			// Gets
542     			bulk ?
543     				fn.call(elems) :
544     				length ? fn(elems[0], key) : emptyGet;
545         };

547         jQuery.ajax = function (url, options) {
548             /// <summary>
549             ///     Perform an asynchronous HTTP (Ajax) request.
550             ///     &#10;1 - jQuery.ajax(url, settings) 
551             ///     &#10;2 - jQuery.ajax(settings)
552             /// </summary>
553             /// <param name="url" type="String">
554             ///     A string containing the URL to which the request is sent.
555             /// </param>
556             /// <param name="options" type="PlainObject">
557             ///     A set of key/value pairs that configure the Ajax request. All settings are optional. A default can be set for any option with $.ajaxSetup(). See jQuery.ajax( settings ) below for a complete list of all settings.
558             /// </param>
559     
560     
561             // If url is an object, simulate pre-1.5 signature
562             if (typeof url === "object") {
563                 options = url;
564                 url = undefined;
565             }
566     
567             // Force options to be an object
568             options = options || {};
569     
570             var transport,
571     			// URL without anti-cache param
572     			cacheURL,
573     			// Response headers
574     			responseHeadersString,
575     			responseHeaders,
576     			// timeout handle
577     			timeoutTimer,
578     			// Cross-domain detection vars
579     			parts,
580     			// To know if global events are to be dispatched
581     			fireGlobals,
582     			// Loop variable
583     			i,
584     			// Create the final options object
585     			s = jQuery.ajaxSetup({}, options),
586     			// Callbacks context
587     			callbackContext = s.context || s,
588     			// Context for global events is callbackContext if it is a DOM node or jQuery collection
589     			globalEventContext = s.context && (callbackContext.nodeType || callbackContext.jquery) ?
590     				jQuery(callbackContext) :
591     				jQuery.event,
592     			// Deferreds
593     			deferred = jQuery.Deferred(),

595     			// Status-dependent callbacks
596     			statusCode = s.statusCode || {},
597     			// Headers (they are sent all at once)
598     			requestHeaders = {},
599     			requestHeadersNames = {},

601     			state = 0,
602     			// Default abort message
603     			strAbort = "canceled",
604     			// Fake xhr
605     			jqXHR = {
606     			    readyState: 0,
607     
608     			    // Builds headers hashtable if needed
609     			    getResponseHeader: function (key) {
610     			        var match;
611     			        if (state === 2) {
612     			            if (!responseHeaders) {
613     			                responseHeaders = {};
614     			                while ((match = rheaders.exec(responseHeadersString))) {
615     			                    responseHeaders[match[1].toLowerCase()] = match[2];
616     			                }
617     			            }
618     			            match = responseHeaders[key.toLowerCase()];
619     			        }
620     			        return match == null ? null : match;
621     			    },
622     
623     			    // Raw string
624     			    getAllResponseHeaders: function () {
625     			        return state === 2 ? responseHeadersString : null;
626     			    },
627     
628     			    // Caches the header
629     			    setRequestHeader: function (name, value) {
630     			        var lname = name.toLowerCase();
631     			        if (!state) {
632     			            name = requestHeadersNames[lname] = requestHeadersNames[lname] || name;
633     			            requestHeaders[name] = value;
634     			        }
635     			        return this;
636     			    },
637     
638     			    // Overrides response content-type header
639     			    overrideMimeType: function (type) {
640     			        if (!state) {
641     			            s.mimeType = type;
642     			        }
643     			        return this;
644     			    },
645     
646     			    // Status-dependent callbacks
647     			    statusCode: function (map) {
648     			        var code;
649     			        if (map) {
650     			            if (state < 2) {
651     			                for (code in map) {
652     			                    // Lazy-add the new callback in a way that preserves old ones
653     			                    statusCode[code] = [statusCode[code], map[code]];
654     			                }
655     			            } else {
656     			                // Execute the appropriate callbacks
657     			                jqXHR.always(map[jqXHR.status]);
658     			            }
659     			        }
660     			        return this;
661     			    },
662     
663     			    // Cancel the request
664     			    abort: function (statusText) {
665     			        var finalText = statusText || strAbort;
666     			        if (transport) {
667     			            transport.abort(finalText);
668     			        }
669     			        done(0, finalText);
670     			        return this;
671     			    }
672     			};
673     
674             // Attach deferreds
675             deferred.promise(jqXHR).complete = completeDeferred.add;
676             jqXHR.success = jqXHR.done;
677             jqXHR.error = jqXHR.fail;
678     
679             // Remove hash character (#7531: and string promotion)
680             // Add protocol if not provided (prefilters might expect it)
681             // Handle falsy url in the settings object (#10093: consistency with old signature)
682             // We also use the url parameter if available
683             s.url = ((url || s.url || ajaxLocation) + "").replace(rhash, "")
684     			.replace(rprotocol, ajaxLocParts[1] + "//");
685     
686             // Alias method option to type as per ticket #12004
687             s.type = options.method || options.type || s.method || s.type;
688     
689             // Extract dataTypes list
690             s.dataTypes = jQuery.trim(s.dataType || "*").toLowerCase().match(core_rnotwhite) || [""];
691     
692             // A cross-domain request is in order when we have a protocol:host:port mismatch
693             if (s.crossDomain == null) {
694                 parts = rurl.exec(s.url.toLowerCase());
695                 s.crossDomain = !!(parts &&
696     				(parts[1] !== ajaxLocParts[1] || parts[2] !== ajaxLocParts[2] ||
697     					(parts[3] || (parts[1] === "http:" ? "80" : "443")) !==
698     						(ajaxLocParts[3] || (ajaxLocParts[1] === "http:" ? "80" : "443")))
699     			);
700             }
701     
702             // Convert data if not already a string
703             if (s.data && s.processData && typeof s.data !== "string") {
704                 s.data = jQuery.param(s.data, s.traditional);
705             }
706     
707             // Apply prefilters
708             inspectPrefiltersOrTransports(prefilters, s, options, jqXHR);
709     
710             // If request was aborted inside a prefilter, stop there
711             if (state === 2) {
712                 return jqXHR;
713             }
714     
715             // We can fire global events as of now if asked to
716             fireGlobals = s.global;
717     
718             // Watch for a new set of requests
719             if (fireGlobals && jQuery.active++ === 0) {
720                 jQuery.event.trigger("ajaxStart");
721             }
722     
723             // Uppercase the type
724             s.type = s.type.toUpperCase();
725     
726             // Determine if request has content
727             s.hasContent = !rnoContent.test(s.type);
728     
729             // Save the URL in case we're toying with the If-Modified-Since
730             // and/or If-None-Match header later on
731             cacheURL = s.url;
732     
733             // More options handling for requests with no content
734             if (!s.hasContent) {
735     
736                 // If data is available, append data to url
737                 if (s.data) {
738                     cacheURL = (s.url += (ajax_rquery.test(cacheURL) ? "&" : "?") + s.data);
739                     // #9682: remove data so that it's not used in an eventual retry
740                     delete s.data;
741                 }
742     
743                 // Add anti-cache in url if needed
744                 if (s.cache === false) {
745                     s.url = rts.test(cacheURL) ?
746     
747     					// If there is already a '_' parameter, set its value
748     					cacheURL.replace(rts, "$1_=" + ajax_nonce++) :
749     
750     					// Otherwise add one to the end
751     					cacheURL + (ajax_rquery.test(cacheURL) ? "&" : "?") + "_=" + ajax_nonce++;
752                 }
753             }
754     
755             // Set the If-Modified-Since and/or If-None-Match header, if in ifModified mode.
756             if (s.ifModified) {
757                 if (jQuery.lastModified[cacheURL]) {
758                     jqXHR.setRequestHeader("If-Modified-Since", jQuery.lastModified[cacheURL]);
759                 }
760                 if (jQuery.etag[cacheURL]) {
761                     jqXHR.setRequestHeader("If-None-Match", jQuery.etag[cacheURL]);
762                 }
763             }
764     
765             // Set the correct header, if data is being sent
766             if (s.data && s.hasContent && s.contentType !== false || options.contentType) {
767                 jqXHR.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", s.contentType);
768             }
769     
770             // Set the Accepts header for the server, depending on the dataType
771             jqXHR.setRequestHeader(
772     			"Accept",
773     			s.dataTypes[0] && s.accepts[s.dataTypes[0]] ?
774     				s.accepts[s.dataTypes[0]] + (s.dataTypes[0] !== "*" ? ", " + allTypes + "; q=0.01" : "") :
775     				s.accepts["*"]
776     		);
777     
778             // Check for headers option
779             for (i in s.headers) {
780                 jqXHR.setRequestHeader(i, s.headers[i]);
781             }
782     
783             // Allow custom headers/mimetypes and early abort
784             if (s.beforeSend && (s.beforeSend.call(callbackContext, jqXHR, s) === false || state === 2)) {
785                 // Abort if not done already and return
786                 return jqXHR.abort();
787             }
788     
789             // aborting is no longer a cancellation
790             strAbort = "abort";
791     
792             // Install callbacks on deferreds
793             for (i in { success: 1, error: 1, complete: 1 }) {
794                 jqXHR[i](s[i]);
795             }
796     
797             // Get transport
798             transport = inspectPrefiltersOrTransports(transports, s, options, jqXHR);
799     
800             // If no transport, we auto-abort
801             if (!transport) {
802                 done(-1, "No Transport");
803             } else {
804                 jqXHR.readyState = 1;
805     
806                 // Send global event
807                 if (fireGlobals) {
808                     globalEventContext.trigger("ajaxSend", [jqXHR, s]);
809                 }
810                 // Timeout
811                 if (s.async && s.timeout > 0) {
812                     timeoutTimer = setTimeout(function () {
813                         jqXHR.abort("timeout");
814                     }, s.timeout);
815                 }
816     
817                 try {
818                     state = 1;
819                     transport.send(requestHeaders, done);
820                 } catch (e) {
821                     // Propagate exception as error if not done
822                     if (state < 2) {
823                         done(-1, e);
824                         // Simply rethrow otherwise
825                     } else {
826                         throw e;
827                     }
828                 }
829             }
830     
831             // Callback for when everything is done
832             function done(status, nativeStatusText, responses, headers) {
833                 var isSuccess, success, error, response, modified,
834     				statusText = nativeStatusText;
835     
836                 // Called once
837                 if (state === 2) {
838                     return;
839                 }
840     
841                 // State is "done" now
842                 state = 2;
843     
844                 // Clear timeout if it exists
845                 if (timeoutTimer) {
846                     clearTimeout(timeoutTimer);
847                 }
848     
849                 // Dereference transport for early garbage collection
850                 // (no matter how long the jqXHR object will be used)
851                 transport = undefined;
852     
853                 // Cache response headers
854                 responseHeadersString = headers || "";
855     
856                 // Set readyState
857                 jqXHR.readyState = status > 0 ? 4 : 0;
858     
859                 // Determine if successful
860                 isSuccess = status >= 200 && status < 300 || status === 304;
861     
862                 // Get response data
863                 if (responses) {
864                     response = ajaxHandleResponses(s, jqXHR, responses);
865                 }
866     
867                 // Convert no matter what (that way responseXXX fields are always set)
868                 response = ajaxConvert(s, response, jqXHR, isSuccess);
869     
870                 // If successful, handle type chaining
871                 if (isSuccess) {
872     
873                     // Set the If-Modified-Since and/or If-None-Match header, if in ifModified mode.
874                     if (s.ifModified) {
875                         modified = jqXHR.getResponseHeader("Last-Modified");
876                         if (modified) {
877                             jQuery.lastModified[cacheURL] = modified;
878                         }
879                         modified = jqXHR.getResponseHeader("etag");
880                         if (modified) {
881                             jQuery.etag[cacheURL] = modified;
882                         }
883                     }
884     
885                     // if no content
886                     if (status === 204) {
887                         statusText = "nocontent";
888     
889                         // if not modified
890                     } else if (status === 304) {
891                         statusText = "notmodified";
892     
893                         // If we have data, let's convert it
894                     } else {
895                         statusText = response.state;
896                         success = response.data;
897                         error = response.error;
898                         isSuccess = !error;
899                     }
900                 } else {
901                     // We extract error from statusText
902                     // then normalize statusText and status for non-aborts
903                     error = statusText;
904                     if (status || !statusText) {
905                         statusText = "error";
906                         if (status < 0) {
907                             status = 0;
908                         }
909                     }
910                 }
911     
912                 // Set data for the fake xhr object
913                 jqXHR.status = status;
914                 jqXHR.statusText = (nativeStatusText || statusText) + "";
915     
916                 // Success/Error
917                 if (isSuccess) {
918                     deferred.resolveWith(callbackContext, [success, statusText, jqXHR]);
919                 } else {
920                     deferred.rejectWith(callbackContext, [jqXHR, statusText, error]);
921                 }
922     
923                 // Status-dependent callbacks
924                 jqXHR.statusCode(statusCode);
925                 statusCode = undefined;
926     
927                 if (fireGlobals) {
928                     globalEventContext.trigger(isSuccess ? "ajaxSuccess" : "ajaxError",
929     					[jqXHR, s, isSuccess ? success : error]);
930                 }
931     
932                 // Complete
933                 completeDeferred.fireWith(callbackContext, [jqXHR, statusText]);
934     
935                 if (fireGlobals) {
936                     globalEventContext.trigger("ajaxComplete", [jqXHR, s]);
937                     // Handle the global AJAX counter
938                     if (!(--jQuery.active)) {
939                         jQuery.event.trigger("ajaxStop");
940                     }
941                 }
942             }
943     
944             return jqXHR;
945         };
946         jQuery.ajaxPrefilter = function (dataTypeExpression, func) {

949             /// </summary>
950             /// <param name="dataTypeExpression" type="String">

957     
958     
959             if (typeof dataTypeExpression !== "string") {
960                 func = dataTypeExpression;
961                 dataTypeExpression = "*";
962             }

964             var dataType,
965     			i = 0,
966     			dataTypes = dataTypeExpression.toLowerCase().match(core_rnotwhite) || [];
967

974                         (structure[dataType] = structure[dataType] || []).unshift(func);
975     
976                         // Otherwise append
977                     } else {
978                         (structure[dataType] = structure[dataType] || []).push(func);
979                     }
980                 }
981             }

1051         jQuery.attr = function (elem, name, value) {
1052     
1053             var hooks, ret,
1054     			nType = elem.nodeType;
1055     
1056             // don't get/set attributes on text, comment and attribute nodes
1057             if (!elem || nType === 3 || nType === 8 || nType === 2) {
1058                 return;
1059             }
1060     
1061             // Fallback to prop when attributes are not supported
1062             if (typeof elem.getAttribute === core_strundefined) {
1063                 return jQuery.prop(elem, name, value);
1064             }
1065     
1066             // All attributes are lowercase
1067             // Grab necessary hook if one is defined
1068             if (nType !== 1 || !jQuery.isXMLDoc(elem)) {
1069                 name = name.toLowerCase();
1070                 hooks = jQuery.attrHooks[name] ||
1071     				(jQuery.expr.match.boolean.test(name) ? boolHook : nodeHook);
1072             }
1073     
1074             if (value !== undefined) {
1075     
1076                 if (value === null) {
1077                     jQuery.removeAttr(elem, name);
1078     
1079                 } else if (hooks && "set" in hooks && (ret = hooks.set(elem, value, name)) !== undefined) {
1080                     return ret;
1081     
1082                 } else {
1083                     elem.setAttribute(name, value + "");
1084                     return value;
1085                 }
1086     
1087             } else if (hooks && "get" in hooks && (ret = hooks.get(elem, name)) !== null) {
1088                 return ret;
1089     
1090             } else {
1091                 ret = jQuery.find.attr(elem, name);
1092     
1093                 // Non-existent attributes return null, we normalize to undefined
1094                 return ret == null ?
1095                     undefined :
1096     				ret;
1097             }
1098         };

1100         jQuery.buildFragment = function (elems, context, scripts, selection) {
1101     
1102             var elem, tmp, tag, wrap, contains, j,
1103     			i = 0,
1104     			l = elems.length,
1105     			fragment = context.createDocumentFragment(),
1106     			nodes = [];
1107     
1108             for (; i < l; i++) {
1109                 elem = elems[i];
1110     
1111                 if (elem || elem === 0) {
1112     
1113                     // Add nodes directly
1114                     if (jQuery.type(elem) === "object") {
1115                         // Support: QtWebKit
1116                         // jQuery.merge because core_push.apply(_, arraylike) throws
1117                         jQuery.merge(nodes, elem.nodeType ? [elem] : elem);
1118     
1119                         // Convert non-html into a text node
1120                     } else if (!rhtml.test(elem)) {
1121                         nodes.push(context.createTextNode(elem));
1122     
1123                         // Convert html into DOM nodes
1124                     } else {
1125                         tmp = tmp || fragment.appendChild(context.createElement("div"));
1126     
1127                         // Deserialize a standard representation
1128                         tag = (rtagName.exec(elem) || ["", ""])[1].toLowerCase();
1129                         wrap = wrapMap[tag] || wrapMap._default;
1130                         tmp.innerHTML = wrap[1] + elem.replace(rxhtmlTag, "<$1></$2>") + wrap[2];
1131     
1132                         // Descend through wrappers to the right content
1133                         j = wrap[0];
1134                         while (j--) {
1135                             tmp = tmp.firstChild;
1136                         }
1137     
1138                         // Support: QtWebKit
1139                         // jQuery.merge because core_push.apply(_, arraylike) throws
1140                         jQuery.merge(nodes, tmp.childNodes);
1141     
1142                         // Remember the top-level container
1143                         tmp = fragment.firstChild;
1144     
1145                         // Fixes #12346
1146                         // Support: Webkit, IE
1147                         tmp.textContent = "";
1148                     }
1149                 }
1150             }
1151     
1152             // Remove wrapper from fragment
1153             fragment.textContent = "";
1154     
1155             i = 0;
1156             while ((elem = nodes[i++])) {
1157     
1158                 // #4087 - If origin and destination elements are the same, and this is
1159                 // that element, do not do anything
1160                 if (selection && jQuery.inArray(elem, selection) !== -1) {
1161                     continue;
1162                 }
1163     
1164                 contains = jQuery.contains(elem.ownerDocument, elem);
1165     
1166                 // Append to fragment
1167                 tmp = getAll(fragment.appendChild(elem), "script");
1168     
1169                 // Preserve script evaluation history
1170                 if (contains) {
1171                     setGlobalEval(tmp);
1172                 }
1173     
1174                 // Capture executables
1175                 if (scripts) {
1176                     j = 0;
1177                     while ((elem = tmp[j++])) {
1178                         if (rscriptType.test(elem.type || "")) {
1179                             scripts.push(elem);
1180                         }
1181                     }
1182                 }
1183             }
1184     
1185             return fragment;
1186         };

1191         jQuery.cleanData = function (elems) {
1192     
1193             var data, elem, type,
1194     			l = elems.length,
1195     			i = 0,
1196     			special = jQuery.event.special;
1197     
1198             for (; i < l; i++) {
1199                 elem = elems[i];
1200     
1201                 if (jQuery.acceptData(elem)) {
1202     
1203                     data = data_priv.access(elem);
1204     
1205                     if (data) {
1206                         for (type in data.events) {
1207                             if (special[type]) {
1208                                 jQuery.event.remove(elem, type);
1209     
1210                                 // This is a shortcut to avoid jQuery.event.remove's overhead
1211                             } else {
1212                                 jQuery.removeEvent(elem, type, data.handle);
1213                             }
1214                         }
1215                     }
1216                 }
1217                 // Discard any remaining `private` and `user` data
1218                 // One day we'll replace the dual arrays with a WeakMap and this won't be an issue.
1219                 // (Splices the data objects out of the internal cache arrays)
1220                 data_user.discard(elem);
1221                 data_priv.discard(elem);
1222             }

1224         jQuery.clone = function (elem, dataAndEvents, deepDataAndEvents) {
1225     
1226             var i, l, srcElements, destElements,
1227     			clone = elem.cloneNode(true),
1228     			inPage = jQuery.contains(elem.ownerDocument, elem);
1229     
1230             // Support: IE >= 9
1231             // Fix Cloning issues
1232             if (!jQuery.support.noCloneChecked && (elem.nodeType === 1 || elem.nodeType === 11) && !jQuery.isXMLDoc(elem)) {
1233     
1234                 // We eschew Sizzle here for performance reasons: http://jsperf.com/getall-vs-sizzle/2
1235                 destElements = getAll(clone);
1236                 srcElements = getAll(elem);
1237     
1238                 for (i = 0, l = srcElements.length; i < l; i++) {
1239                     fixInput(srcElements[i], destElements[i]);
1240                 }
1241             }
1242     
1243             // Copy the events from the original to the clone
1244             if (dataAndEvents) {
1245                 if (deepDataAndEvents) {
1246                     srcElements = srcElements || getAll(elem);
1247                     destElements = destElements || getAll(clone);
1248     
1249                     for (i = 0, l = srcElements.length; i < l; i++) {
1250                         cloneCopyEvent(srcElements[i], destElements[i]);
1251                     }
1252                 } else {
1253                     cloneCopyEvent(elem, clone);
1254                 }
1255             }
1256     
1257             // Preserve script evaluation history
1258             destElements = getAll(clone, "script");
1259             if (destElements.length > 0) {
1260                 setGlobalEval(destElements, !inPage && getAll(elem, "script"));
1261             }
1262     
1263             // Return the cloned set
1264             return clone;
1265         };

1284         jQuery.css = function (elem, name, extra, styles) {
1285

1291

1295

1300

1302             if (val === undefined) {

1312             if (extra === "" || extra) {
1313                 num = parseFloat(val);
1314                 return extra === true || jQuery.isNumeric(num) ? num || 0 : val;
1315             }
1316             return val;

1365         jQuery.dequeue = function (elem, type) {
1366             /// <summary>
1367             ///     Execute the next function on the queue for the matched element.
1368             /// </summary>
1369             /// <param name="elem" domElement="true">
1370             ///     A DOM element from which to remove and execute a queued function.
1371             /// </param>
1372             /// <param name="type" type="String">
1373             ///     A string containing the name of the queue. Defaults to fx, the standard effects queue.
1374             /// </param>
1375             /// <returns type="undefined" />
1376     
1377             type = type || "fx";
1378     
1379             var queue = jQuery.queue(elem, type),
1380     			startLength = queue.length,
1381     			fn = queue.shift(),
1382     			hooks = jQuery._queueHooks(elem, type),
1383     			next = function () {
1384     			    jQuery.dequeue(elem, type);
1385     			};
1386     
1387             // If the fx queue is dequeued, always remove the progress sentinel
1388             if (fn === "inprogress") {
1389                 fn = queue.shift();
1390                 startLength--;
1391             }
1392     
1393             hooks.cur = fn;
1394             if (fn) {
1395     
1396                 // Add a progress sentinel to prevent the fx queue from being
1397                 // automatically dequeued
1398                 if (type === "fx") {
1399                     queue.unshift("inprogress");
1400                 }
1401     
1402                 // clear up the last queue stop function
1403                 delete hooks.stop;

1426         jQuery.each = function (obj, callback, args) {
1427             /// <summary>
1428             ///     A generic iterator function, which can be used to seamlessly iterate over both objects and arrays. Arrays and array-like objects with a length property (such as a function's arguments object) are iterated by numeric index, from 0 to length-1. Other objects are iterated via their named properties.
1429             /// </summary>
1430             /// <param name="obj" type="Object">
1431             ///     The object or array to iterate over.
1432             /// </param>
1433             /// <param name="callback" type="Function">
1434             ///     The function that will be executed on every object.
1435             /// </param>
1436             /// <returns type="Object" />

1439     			i = 0,
1440     			length = obj.length,
1441     			isArray = isArraylike(obj);

1444                 if (isArray) {
1445                     for (; i < length; i++) {
1446                         value = callback.apply(obj[i], args);
1447     
1448                         if (value === false) {
1449                             break;
1450                         }
1451                     }
1452                 } else {
1453                     for (i in obj) {
1454                         value = callback.apply(obj[i], args);
1455     
1456                         if (value === false) {
1457                             break;
1458                         }
1459                     }
1460                 }
1461     
1462                 // A special, fast, case for the most common use of each
1463             } else {
1464                 if (isArray) {
1465                     for (; i < length; i++) {
1466                         value = callback.call(obj[i], i, obj[i]);
1467     
1468                         if (value === false) {
1469                             break;
1470                         }
1471                     }
1472                 } else {
1473                     for (i in obj) {
1474                         value = callback.call(obj[i], i, obj[i]);
1475     
1476                         if (value === false) {
1477                             break;
1478                         }
1479                     }
1480                 }
1481             }
1482     
1483             return obj;

1519         jQuery.extend = function () {
1520             /// <summary>
1521             ///     Merge the contents of two or more objects together into the first object.
1522             ///     &#10;1 - jQuery.extend(target, object1, objectN) 
1523             ///     &#10;2 - jQuery.extend(deep, target, object1, objectN)
1524             /// </summary>
1525             /// <param name="" type="Boolean">
1526             ///     If true, the merge becomes recursive (aka. deep copy).
1527             /// </param>
1528             /// <param name="" type="Object">
1529             ///     The object to extend. It will receive the new properties.
1530             /// </param>
1531             /// <param name="" type="Object">
1532             ///     An object containing additional properties to merge in.
1533             /// </param>
1534             /// <param name="" type="Object">
1535             ///     Additional objects containing properties to merge in.
1536             /// </param>
1537             /// <returns type="Object" />
1538     
1539             var options, name, src, copy, copyIsArray, clone,
1540                 target = arguments[0] || {},
1541                 i = 1,
1542                 length = arguments.length,
1543                 deep = false;
1544     
1545             // Handle a deep copy situation
1546             if (typeof target === "boolean") {
1547                 deep = target;
1548                 target = arguments[1] || {};
1549                 // skip the boolean and the target
1550                 i = 2;
1551             }
1552     
1553             // Handle case when target is a string or something (possible in deep copy)
1554             if (typeof target !== "object" && !jQuery.isFunction(target)) {
1555                 target = {};
1556             }
1557     
1558             // extend jQuery itself if only one argument is passed
1559             if (length === i) {
1560                 target = this;
1561                 --i;
1562             }
1563     
1564             for (; i < length; i++) {
1565                 // Only deal with non-null/undefined values
1566                 if ((options = arguments[i]) != null) {
1567                     // Extend the base object
1568                     for (name in options) {
1569                         src = target[name];
1570                         copy = options[name];
1571     
1572                         // Prevent never-ending loop
1573                         if (target === copy) {
1574                             continue;
1575                         }
1576     
1577                         // Recurse if we're merging plain objects or arrays
1578                         if (deep && copy && (jQuery.isPlainObject(copy) || (copyIsArray = jQuery.isArray(copy)))) {
1579                             if (copyIsArray) {
1580                                 copyIsArray = false;
1581                                 clone = src && jQuery.isArray(src) ? src : [];
1582     
1583                             } else {
1584                                 clone = src && jQuery.isPlainObject(src) ? src : {};
1585                             }
1586     
1587                             // Never move original objects, clone them
1588                             target[name] = jQuery.extend(deep, clone, copy);
1589     
1590                             // Don't bring in undefined values
1591                         } else if (copy !== undefined) {
1592                             target[name] = copy;
1593                         }
1594                     }
1595                 }
1596             }
1597     
1598             // Return the modified object
1599             return target;
1600         };

1615         jQuery.find = function Sizzle(selector, context, results, seed) {
1616     
1617             var match, elem, m, nodeType,
1618                 // QSA vars
1619                 i, groups, old, nid, newContext, newSelector;
1620     
1621             if ((context ? context.ownerDocument || context : preferredDoc) !== document) {
1622                 setDocument(context);
1623             }
1624     
1625             context = context || document;
1626             results = results || [];
1627     
1628             if (!selector || typeof selector !== "string") {
1629                 return results;
1630             }
1631     
1632             if ((nodeType = context.nodeType) !== 1 && nodeType !== 9) {
1633                 return [];
1634             }
1635     
1636             if (documentIsHTML && !seed) {
1637     
1638                 // Shortcuts
1639                 if ((match = rquickExpr.exec(selector))) {
1640                     // Speed-up: Sizzle("#ID")
1641                     if ((m = match[1])) {
1642                         if (nodeType === 9) {
1643                             elem = context.getElementById(m);
1644                             // Check parentNode to catch when Blackberry 4.6 returns
1645                             // nodes that are no longer in the document #6963
1646                             if (elem && elem.parentNode) {
1647                                 // Handle the case where IE, Opera, and Webkit return items
1648                                 // by name instead of ID
1649                                 if (elem.id === m) {
1650                                     results.push(elem);
1651                                     return results;
1652                                 }
1653                             } else {
1654                                 return results;
1655                             }
1656                         } else {
1657                             // Context is not a document
1658                             if (context.ownerDocument && (elem = context.ownerDocument.getElementById(m)) &&
1659                                 contains(context, elem) && elem.id === m) {
1660                                 results.push(elem);
1661                                 return results;
1662                             }
1663                         }
1664     
1665                         // Speed-up: Sizzle("TAG")
1666                     } else if (match[2]) {
1667                         push.apply(results, context.getElementsByTagName(selector));
1668                         return results;
1669     
1670                         // Speed-up: Sizzle(".CLASS")
1671                     } else if ((m = match[3]) && support.getElementsByClassName && context.getElementsByClassName) {
1672                         push.apply(results, context.getElementsByClassName(m));
1673                         return results;
1674                     }
1675                 }
1676     
1677                 // QSA path
1678                 if (support.qsa && (!rbuggyQSA || !rbuggyQSA.test(selector))) {
1679                     nid = old = expando;
1680                     newContext = context;
1681                     newSelector = nodeType === 9 && selector;
1682     
1683                     // qSA works strangely on Element-rooted queries
1684                     // We can work around this by specifying an extra ID on the root
1685                     // and working up from there (Thanks to Andrew Dupont for the technique)
1686                     // IE 8 doesn't work on object elements
1687                     if (nodeType === 1 && context.nodeName.toLowerCase() !== "object") {
1688                         groups = tokenize(selector);
1689     
1690                         if ((old = context.getAttribute("id"))) {
1691                             nid = old.replace(rescape, "\\$&");
1692                         } else {
1693                             context.setAttribute("id", nid);
1694                         }
1695                         nid = "[id='" + nid + "'] ";
1696     
1697                         i = groups.length;
1698                         while (i--) {
1699                             groups[i] = nid + toSelector(groups[i]);
1700                         }
1701                         newContext = rsibling.test(selector) && context.parentNode || context;
1702                         newSelector = groups.join(",");
1703                     }
1704     
1705                     if (newSelector) {
1706                         try {
1707                             push.apply(results,
1708                                 newContext.querySelectorAll(newSelector)
1709                             );
1710                             return results;
1711                         } catch (qsaError) {
1712                         } finally {
1713                             if (!old) {
1714                                 context.removeAttribute("id");
1715                             }
1716                         }
1717                     }
1718                 }
1719             }
1720     
1721             // All others
1722             return select(selector.replace(rtrim, "$1"), context, results, seed);
1723         };

2026         jQuery.map = function (elems, callback, arg) {
2027             /// <summary>

2029             ///     &#10;1 - jQuery.map(array, callback(elementOfArray, indexInArray))

2321             ///     &#10;1 - jQuery.proxy(function, context) 
2322             ///     &#10;2 - jQuery.proxy(context, name)

2327             ///     The function whose context will be changed.
2328             /// </param>

2330             ///     The object to which the context (this) of the function should be set.
2331             /// </param>

2333             ///     Any number of arguments to be passed to the function referenced in the function argument.

2340                 tmp = fn[context];
2341                 context = fn;

2343             }

2700         jQuery.when = function (subordinate /* , ..., subordinateN */) {
2701             /// <summary>
2702             ///     Provides a way to execute callback functions based on one or more objects, usually Deferred objects that represent asynchronous events.
2703             /// </summary>
2704             /// <param name="subordinate/*" type="Deferred">
2705             ///     One or more Deferred objects, or plain JavaScript objects.
2706             /// </param>
2707             /// <returns type="Promise" />
2708     
2709             var i = 0,
2710     			resolveValues = core_slice.call(arguments),
2711     			length = resolveValues.length,
2712     
2713     			// the count of uncompleted subordinates
2714     			remaining = length !== 1 || (subordinate && jQuery.isFunction(subordinate.promise)) ? length : 0,
2715     
2716     			// the master Deferred. If resolveValues consist of only a single Deferred, just use that.
2717     			deferred = remaining === 1 ? subordinate : jQuery.Deferred(),
2718     
2719     			// Update function for both resolve and progress values
2720     			updateFunc = function (i, contexts, values) {
2721     			    return function (value) {
2722     			        contexts[i] = this;
2723     			        values[i] = arguments.length > 1 ? core_slice.call(arguments) : value;
2724     			        if (values === progressValues) {
2725     			            deferred.notifyWith(contexts, values);
2726     			        } else if (!(--remaining)) {
2727     			            deferred.resolveWith(contexts, values);
2728     			        }
2729     			    };
2730     			},
2731     
2732     			progressValues, progressContexts, resolveContexts;
2733     
2734             // add listeners to Deferred subordinates; treat others as resolved
2735             if (length > 1) {
2736                 progressValues = new Array(length);
2737                 progressContexts = new Array(length);
2738                 resolveContexts = new Array(length);
2739                 for (; i < length; i++) {
2740                     if (resolveValues[i] && jQuery.isFunction(resolveValues[i].promise)) {
2741                         resolveValues[i].promise()
2742     						.done(updateFunc(i, resolveContexts, resolveValues))

3389         jQuery.prototype.data = function (key, value) {
3390             /// <summary>
3391             ///     1: Store arbitrary data associated with the matched elements.
3392             ///     &#10;    1.1 - data(key, value) 
3393             ///     &#10;    1.2 - data(obj)
3394             ///     &#10;2: Return the value at the named data store for the first element in the jQuery collection, as set by data(name, value) or by an HTML5 data-* attribute.
3395             ///     &#10;    2.1 - data(key) 
3396             ///     &#10;    2.2 - data()
3397             /// </summary>
3398             /// <param name="key" type="String">
3399             ///     A string naming the piece of data to set.
3400             /// </param>
3401             /// <param name="value" type="Object">
3402             ///     The new data value; it can be any Javascript type including Array or Object.
3403             /// </param>
3404             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
3405     
3406             var attrs, name,
3407     			elem = this[0],
3408     			i = 0,
3409     			data = null;
3410     
3411             // Gets all values
3412             if (key === undefined) {
3413                 if (this.length) {
3414                     data = data_user.get(elem);
3415     
3416                     if (elem.nodeType === 1 && !data_priv.get(elem, "hasDataAttrs")) {
3417                         attrs = elem.attributes;
3418                         for (; i < attrs.length; i++) {
3419                             name = attrs[i].name;
3420     
3421                             if (name.indexOf("data-") === 0) {
3422                                 name = jQuery.camelCase(name.substring(5));
3423                                 dataAttr(elem, name, data[name]);
3424                             }
3425                         }
3426                         data_priv.set(elem, "hasDataAttrs", true);
3427                     }
3428                 }
3429     
3430                 return data;
3431             }
3432     
3433             // Sets multiple values
3434             if (typeof key === "object") {
3435                 return this.each(function () {
3436                     data_user.set(this, key);
3437                 });
3438             }
3439     
3440             return jQuery.access(this, function (value) {
3441                 var data,
3442     				camelKey = jQuery.camelCase(key);
3443     
3444                 // The calling jQuery object (element matches) is not empty
3445                 // (and therefore has an element appears at this[ 0 ]) and the
3446                 // `value` parameter was not undefined. An empty jQuery object
3447                 // will result in `undefined` for elem = this[ 0 ] which will
3448                 // throw an exception if an attempt to read a data cache is made.
3449                 if (elem && value === undefined) {
3450                     // Attempt to get data from the cache
3451                     // with the key as-is
3452                     data = data_user.get(elem, key);
3453                     if (data !== undefined) {
3454                         return data;
3455                     }
3456     
3457                     // Attempt to get data from the cache
3458                     // with the key camelized
3459                     data = data_user.get(elem, camelKey);
3460                     if (data !== undefined) {
3461                         return data;
3462                     }
3463     
3464                     // Attempt to "discover" the data in
3465                     // HTML5 custom data-* attrs
3466                     data = dataAttr(elem, camelKey, undefined);
3467                     if (data !== undefined) {
3468                         return data;
3469                     }
3470     
3471                     // We tried really hard, but the data doesn't exist.
3472                     return;
3473                 }
3474     
3475                 // Set the data...
3476                 this.each(function () {
3477                     // First, attempt to store a copy or reference of any
3478                     // data that might've been store with a camelCased key.
3479                     var data = data_user.get(this, camelKey);
3480     
3481                     // For HTML5 data-* attribute interop, we have to
3482                     // store property names with dashes in a camelCase form.
3483                     // This might not apply to all properties...*
3484                     data_user.set(this, camelKey, value);
3485     
3486                     // *... In the case of properties that might _actually_
3487                     // have dashes, we need to also store a copy of that
3488                     // unchanged property.
3489                     if (key.indexOf("-") !== -1 && data !== undefined) {
3490                         data_user.set(this, key, value);
3491                     }
3492                 });
3493             }, null, value, arguments.length > 1, null, true);
3494         };

3583         jQuery.prototype.domManip = function (args, callback, allowIntersection) {
3584     
3585     
3586             // Flatten any nested arrays
3587             args = core_concat.apply([], args);

3589             var fragment, first, scripts, hasScripts, node, doc,

3598             if (isFunction || !(l <= 1 || typeof value !== "string" || jQuery.support.checkClone || !rchecked.test(value))) {

3600                     var self = set.eq(index);

3607

3610                 first = fragment.firstChild;
3611     
3612                 if (fragment.childNodes.length === 1) {

3614                 }
3615     
3616                 if (first) {
3617                     scripts = jQuery.map(getAll(fragment, "script"), disableScript);
3618                     hasScripts = scripts.length;
3619     
3620                     // Use the original fragment for the last item instead of the first because it can end up
3621                     // being emptied incorrectly in certain situations (#8070).
3622                     for (; i < l; i++) {
3623                         node = fragment;
3624

3632                                 jQuery.merge(scripts, getAll(node, "script"));
3633                             }
3634                         }
3635

3637                     }
3638     
3639                     if (hasScripts) {
3640                         doc = scripts[scripts.length - 1].ownerDocument;
3641     
3642                         // Reenable scripts
3643                         jQuery.map(scripts, restoreScript);
3644

3646                         for (i = 0; i < hasScripts; i++) {
3647                             node = scripts[i];

3649     							!data_priv.access(node, "globalEval") && jQuery.contains(doc, node)) {
3650

3652                                     // Hope ajax is available...
3653                                     jQuery._evalUrl(node.src);
3654                                 } else {
3655                                     jQuery.globalEval(node.textContent.replace(rcleanScript, ""));
3656                                 }
3657                             }
3658                         }
3659                     }
3660                 }
3661             }
3662

3664         };

3739         jQuery.prototype.extend = function () {
3740     
3741             var options, name, src, copy, copyIsArray, clone,
3742                 target = arguments[0] || {},
3743                 i = 1,
3744                 length = arguments.length,
3745                 deep = false;
3746     
3747             // Handle a deep copy situation
3748             if (typeof target === "boolean") {
3749                 deep = target;
3750                 target = arguments[1] || {};
3751                 // skip the boolean and the target
3752                 i = 2;
3753             }
3754     
3755             // Handle case when target is a string or something (possible in deep copy)
3756             if (typeof target !== "object" && !jQuery.isFunction(target)) {
3757                 target = {};
3758             }
3759     
3760             // extend jQuery itself if only one argument is passed
3761             if (length === i) {
3762                 target = this;
3763                 --i;
3764             }
3765     
3766             for (; i < length; i++) {
3767                 // Only deal with non-null/undefined values
3768                 if ((options = arguments[i]) != null) {
3769                     // Extend the base object
3770                     for (name in options) {
3771                         src = target[name];
3772                         copy = options[name];
3773     
3774                         // Prevent never-ending loop
3775                         if (target === copy) {
3776                             continue;
3777                         }
3778     
3779                         // Recurse if we're merging plain objects or arrays
3780                         if (deep && copy && (jQuery.isPlainObject(copy) || (copyIsArray = jQuery.isArray(copy)))) {
3781                             if (copyIsArray) {
3782                                 copyIsArray = false;
3783                                 clone = src && jQuery.isArray(src) ? src : [];
3784     
3785                             } else {
3786                                 clone = src && jQuery.isPlainObject(src) ? src : {};
3787                             }
3788     
3789                             // Never move original objects, clone them
3790                             target[name] = jQuery.extend(deep, clone, copy);
3791     
3792                             // Don't bring in undefined values
3793                         } else if (copy !== undefined) {
3794                             target[name] = copy;
3795                         }
3796                     }
3797                 }
3798             }
3799     
3800             // Return the modified object
3801             return target;
3802         };

3940         jQuery.prototype.finish = function (type) {
3941             /// <summary>
3942             ///     Stop the currently-running animation, remove all queued animations, and complete all animations for the matched elements.
3943             /// </summary>
3944             /// <param name="type" type="String">
3945             ///     The name of the queue in which to stop animations.
3946             /// </param>
3947             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
3948     
3949             if (type !== false) {
3950                 type = type || "fx";
3951             }
3952             return this.each(function () {
3953                 var index,
3954     				data = data_priv.get(this),
3955     				queue = data[type + "queue"],
3956     				hooks = data[type + "queueHooks"],
3957     				timers = jQuery.timers,
3958     				length = queue ? queue.length : 0;
3959     
3960                 // enable finishing flag on private data
3961                 data.finish = true;
3962     
3963                 // empty the queue first
3964                 jQuery.queue(this, type, []);
3965     
3966                 if (hooks && hooks.cur && hooks.cur.finish) {
3967                     hooks.cur.finish.call(this);
3968                 }
3969     
3970                 // look for any active animations, and finish them
3971                 for (index = timers.length; index--;) {
3972                     if (timers[index].elem === this && timers[index].queue === type) {
3973                         timers[index].anim.stop(true);
3974                         timers.splice(index, 1);
3975                     }
3976                 }

3978                 // look for any animations in the old queue and finish them
3979                 for (index = 0; index < length; index++) {
3980                     if (queue[index] && queue[index].finish) {
3981                         queue[index].finish.call(this);
3982                     }
3983                 }
3984     
3985                 // turn off finishing flag
3986                 delete data.finish;
3987             });

4279         jQuery.prototype.init = function (selector, context, rootjQuery) {
4280     
4281             var match, elem;
4282     
4283             // HANDLE: $(""), $(null), $(undefined), $(false)
4284             if (!selector) {
4285                 return this;
4286             }
4287     
4288             // Handle HTML strings
4289             if (typeof selector === "string") {
4290                 if (selector.charAt(0) === "<" && selector.charAt(selector.length - 1) === ">" && selector.length >= 3) {
4291                     // Assume that strings that start and end with <> are HTML and skip the regex check
4292                     match = [null, selector, null];
4293     
4294                 } else {
4295                     match = rquickExpr.exec(selector);
4296                 }
4297     
4298                 // Match html or make sure no context is specified for #id
4299                 if (match && (match[1] || !context)) {
4300     
4301                     // HANDLE: $(html) -> $(array)
4302                     if (match[1]) {
4303                         context = context instanceof jQuery ? context[0] : context;
4304     
4305                         // scripts is true for back-compat
4306                         jQuery.merge(this, jQuery.parseHTML(
4307     						match[1],
4308     						context && context.nodeType ? context.ownerDocument || context : document,
4309     						true
4310     					));
4311     
4312                         // HANDLE: $(html, props)
4313                         if (rsingleTag.test(match[1]) && jQuery.isPlainObject(context)) {
4314                             for (match in context) {
4315                                 // Properties of context are called as methods if possible
4316                                 if (jQuery.isFunction(this[match])) {
4317                                     this[match](context[match]);
4318     
4319                                     // ...and otherwise set as attributes
4320                                 } else {
4321                                     this.attr(match, context[match]);
4322                                 }
4323                             }
4324                         }
4325     
4326                         return this;
4327     
4328                         // HANDLE: $(#id)
4329                     } else {
4330                         elem = document.getElementById(match[2]);
4331     
4332                         // Check parentNode to catch when Blackberry 4.6 returns
4333                         // nodes that are no longer in the document #6963
4334                         if (elem && elem.parentNode) {
4335                             // Inject the element directly into the jQuery object
4336                             this.length = 1;
4337                             this[0] = elem;
4338                         }
4339     
4340                         this.context = document;
4341                         this.selector = selector;
4342                         return this;
4343                     }
4344     
4345                     // HANDLE: $(expr, $(...))
4346                 } else if (!context || context.jquery) {
4347                     return (context || rootjQuery).find(selector);
4348     
4349                     // HANDLE: $(expr, context)
4350                     // (which is just equivalent to: $(context).find(expr)
4351                 } else {
4352                     return this.constructor(context).find(selector);
4353                 }
4354     
4355                 // HANDLE: $(DOMElement)
4356             } else if (selector.nodeType) {
4357                 this.context = this[0] = selector;
4358                 this.length = 1;
4359                 return this;
4360     
4361                 // HANDLE: $(function)
4362                 // Shortcut for document ready
4363             } else if (jQuery.isFunction(selector)) {
4364                 return rootjQuery.ready(selector);
4365             }
4366     
4367             if (selector.selector !== undefined) {
4368                 this.selector = selector.selector;
4369                 this.context = selector.context;
4370             }
4371     
4372             return jQuery.makeArray(selector, this);
4373         };

4933         jQuery.prototype.off = function (types, selector, fn) {
