5044         jQuery.prototype.on = function (types, selector, data, fn, /*INTERNAL*/ one) {
5045             /// <summary>
5046             ///     Attach an event handler function for one or more events to the selected elements.
5047             ///     &#10;1 - on(events, selector, data, handler(eventObject)) 
5048             ///     &#10;2 - on(events, selector, data)
5049             /// </summary>
5050             /// <param name="types" type="String">
5051             ///     One or more space-separated event types and optional namespaces, such as "click" or "keydown.myPlugin".
5052             /// </param>
5053             /// <param name="selector" type="String">
5054             ///     A selector string to filter the descendants of the selected elements that trigger the event. If the selector is null or omitted, the event is always triggered when it reaches the selected element.
5055             /// </param>
5056             /// <param name="data" type="Anything">
5057             ///     Data to be passed to the handler in event.data when an event is triggered.
5058             /// </param>
5059             /// <param name="fn" type="Function">
5060             ///     A function to execute when the event is triggered. The value false is also allowed as a shorthand for a function that simply does return false.
5061             /// </param>
5062             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
5063     
5064             var origFn, type;
5065     
5066             // Types can be a map of types/handlers
5067             if (typeof types === "object") {
5068                 // ( types-Object, selector, data )
5069                 if (typeof selector !== "string") {
5070                     // ( types-Object, data )
5071                     data = data || selector;
5072                     selector = undefined;
5073                 }
5074                 for (type in types) {
5075                     this.on(type, selector, data, types[type], one);
5076                 }
5077                 return this;
5078             }
5079     
5080             if (data == null && fn == null) {
5081                 // ( types, fn )
5082                 fn = selector;
5083                 data = selector = undefined;
5084             } else if (fn == null) {
5085                 if (typeof selector === "string") {
5086                     // ( types, selector, fn )
5087                     fn = data;
5088                     data = undefined;
5089                 } else {
5090                     // ( types, data, fn )
5091                     fn = data;
5092                     data = selector;
5093                     selector = undefined;
5094                 }
5095             }
5096             if (fn === false) {
5097                 fn = returnFalse;
5098             } else if (!fn) {
5099                 return this;
5100             }
5101     
5102             if (one === 1) {
5103                 origFn = fn;
5104                 fn = function (event) {
5105                     // Can use an empty set, since event contains the info
5106                     jQuery().off(event);
5107                     return origFn.apply(this, arguments);
5108                 };
5109                 // Use same guid so caller can remove using origFn
5110                 fn.guid = origFn.guid || (origFn.guid = jQuery.guid++);
5111             }
5112             return this.each(function () {
5113                 jQuery.event.add(this, types, fn, data, selector);
5114             });
5115         };

5139         jQuery.prototype.outerHeight = function (margin, value) {
5140             /// <summary>
5141             ///     Get the current computed height for the first element in the set of matched elements, including padding, border, and optionally margin. Returns an integer (without "px") representation of the value or null if called on an empty set of elements.
5142             /// </summary>
5143             /// <param name="margin" type="Boolean">
5144             ///     A Boolean indicating whether to include the element's margin in the calculation.
5145             /// </param>
5146             /// <returns type="Number" />
5147     
5148             var chainable = arguments.length && (defaultExtra || typeof margin !== "boolean"),
5149                 extra = defaultExtra || (margin === true || value === true ? "margin" : "border");
5150     
5151             return jQuery.access(this, function (elem, type, value) {
5152                 var doc;
5153     
5154                 if (jQuery.isWindow(elem)) {
5155                     // As of 5/8/2012 this will yield incorrect results for Mobile Safari, but there
5156                     // isn't a whole lot we can do. See pull request at this URL for discussion:
5157                     // https://github.com/jquery/jquery/pull/764
5158                     return elem.document.documentElement["client" + name];
5159                 }
5160     
5161                 // Get document width or height
5162                 if (elem.nodeType === 9) {
5163                     doc = elem.documentElement;
5164     
5165                     // Either scroll[Width/Height] or offset[Width/Height] or client[Width/Height],
5166                     // whichever is greatest
5167                     return Math.max(
5168                         elem.body["scroll" + name], doc["scroll" + name],
5169                         elem.body["offset" + name], doc["offset" + name],
5170                         doc["client" + name]
5171                     );
5172                 }
5173     
5174                 return value === undefined ?
5175                     // Get width or height on the element, requesting but not forcing parseFloat
5176                     jQuery.css(elem, type, extra) :
5177     
5178                     // Set width or height on the element
5179                     jQuery.style(elem, type, value, extra);
5180             }, type, chainable ? margin : undefined, chainable, null);
5181         };

5218                     // Get width or height on the element, requesting but not forcing parseFloat
5219                     jQuery.css(elem, type, extra) :

5329         jQuery.prototype.position = function () {
5330             /// <summary>
5331             ///     Get the current coordinates of the first element in the set of matched elements, relative to the offset parent.
5332             /// </summary>
5333             /// <returns type="Object" />

5361             }

5365                 top: offset.top - parentOffset.top - jQuery.css(elem, "marginTop", true),

5520         jQuery.prototype.promise = function (type, obj) {
5521             /// <summary>
5522             ///     Return a Promise object to observe when all actions of a certain type bound to the collection, queued or not, have finished.
5523             /// </summary>
5524             /// <param name="type" type="String">
5525             ///     The type of queue that needs to be observed.
5526             /// </param>
5527             /// <param name="obj" type="PlainObject">
5528             ///     Object onto which the promise methods have to be attached
5529             /// </param>
5530             /// <returns type="Promise" />
5531     
5532             var tmp,
5533     			count = 1,
5534     			defer = jQuery.Deferred(),
5535     			elements = this,
5536     			i = this.length,
5537     			resolve = function () {
5538     			    if (!(--count)) {
5539     			        defer.resolveWith(elements, [elements]);
5540     			    }
5541     			};
5542     
5543             if (typeof type !== "string") {
5544                 obj = type;
5545                 type = undefined;
5546             }
5547             type = type || "fx";
5548     
5549             while (i--) {
5550                 tmp = data_priv.get(elements[i], type + "queueHooks");
5551                 if (tmp && tmp.empty) {
5552                     count++;
5553                     tmp.empty.add(resolve);
5554                 }
5555             }
5556             resolve();
5557             return defer.promise(obj);
5558         };

5579             /// <summary>

5606         jQuery.prototype.queue = function (type, data) {
5607             /// <summary>
5608             ///     1: Show the queue of functions to be executed on the matched elements.
5609             ///     &#10;    1.1 - queue(queueName)
5610             ///     &#10;2: Manipulate the queue of functions to be executed, once for each matched element.
5611             ///     &#10;    2.1 - queue(queueName, newQueue) 
5612             ///     &#10;    2.2 - queue(queueName, callback( next ))
5613             /// </summary>
5614             /// <param name="type" type="String">
5615             ///     A string containing the name of the queue. Defaults to fx, the standard effects queue.
5616             /// </param>
5617             /// <param name="data" type="Array">
5618             ///     An array of functions to replace the current queue contents.
5619             /// </param>
5620             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
5621     
5622             var setter = 2;
5623     
5624             if (typeof type !== "string") {
5625                 data = type;
5626                 type = "fx";
5627                 setter--;
5628             }
5629     
5630             if (arguments.length < setter) {
5631                 return jQuery.queue(this[0], type);
5632             }
5633     
5634             return data === undefined ?
5635     			this :
5636     			this.each(function () {
5637     			    var queue = jQuery.queue(this, type, data);
5638     
5639     			    // ensure a hooks for this queue
5640     			    jQuery._queueHooks(this, type);
5641     
5642     			    if (type === "fx" && queue[0] !== "inprogress") {
5643     			        jQuery.dequeue(this, type);
5644     			    }
5645     			});
5646         };

6129         jQuery.prototype.stop = function (type, clearQueue, gotoEnd) {
6130             /// <summary>
6131             ///     Stop the currently-running animation on the matched elements.
6132             ///     &#10;1 - stop(clearQueue, jumpToEnd) 
6133             ///     &#10;2 - stop(queue, clearQueue, jumpToEnd)
6134             /// </summary>
6135             /// <param name="type" type="String">
6136             ///     The name of the queue in which to stop animations.
6137             /// </param>
6138             /// <param name="clearQueue" type="Boolean">
6139             ///     A Boolean indicating whether to remove queued animation as well. Defaults to false.
6140             /// </param>
6141             /// <param name="gotoEnd" type="Boolean">
6142             ///     A Boolean indicating whether to complete the current animation immediately. Defaults to false.
6143             /// </param>
6144             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6145     
6146             var stopQueue = function (hooks) {
6147                 var stop = hooks.stop;
6148                 delete hooks.stop;
6149                 stop(gotoEnd);
6150             };
6151     
6152             if (typeof type !== "string") {
6153                 gotoEnd = clearQueue;
6154                 clearQueue = type;
6155                 type = undefined;
6156             }
6157             if (clearQueue && type !== false) {
6158                 this.queue(type || "fx", []);
6159             }
6160     
6161             return this.each(function () {
6162                 var dequeue = true,
6163     				index = type != null && type + "queueHooks",
6164     				timers = jQuery.timers,
6165     				data = data_priv.get(this);
6166     
6167                 if (index) {
6168                     if (data[index] && data[index].stop) {
6169                         stopQueue(data[index]);
6170                     }
6171                 } else {
6172                     for (index in data) {
6173                         if (data[index] && data[index].stop && rrun.test(index)) {
6174                             stopQueue(data[index]);
6175                         }
6176                     }
6177                 }
6178     
6179                 for (index = timers.length; index--;) {
6180                     if (timers[index].elem === this && (type == null || timers[index].queue === type)) {
6181                         timers[index].anim.stop(gotoEnd);
6182                         dequeue = false;
6183                         timers.splice(index, 1);
6184                     }
6185                 }
6186     
6187                 // start the next in the queue if the last step wasn't forced
6188                 // timers currently will call their complete callbacks, which will dequeue
6189                 // but only if they were gotoEnd
6190                 if (dequeue || !gotoEnd) {
6191                     jQuery.dequeue(this, type);
6192                 }
6193             });
6194         };

6266         jQuery.prototype.toggleClass = function (value, stateVal) {
6267             /// <summary>
6268             ///     Add or remove one or more classes from each element in the set of matched elements, depending on either the class's presence or the value of the switch argument.
6269             ///     &#10;1 - toggleClass(className) 
6270             ///     &#10;2 - toggleClass(className, switch) 
6271             ///     &#10;3 - toggleClass(switch) 
6272             ///     &#10;4 - toggleClass(function(index, class, switch), switch)
6273             /// </summary>

6276             /// </param>
6277             /// <param name="stateVal" type="Boolean">
6278             ///     A Boolean (not just truthy/falsy) value to determine whether the class should be added or removed.
6279             /// </param>
6280             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6281

6283     			isBool = typeof stateVal === "boolean";

6292                 if (type === "string") {

6297     					state = stateVal,
6298     					classNames = value.match(core_rnotwhite) || [];

6301                         // check each className given, space separated list
6302                         state = isBool ? state : !self.hasClass(className);
6303                         self[state ? "addClass" : "removeClass"](className);
6304                     }
6305     
6306                     // Toggle whole class name
6307                 } else if (type === core_strundefined || type === "boolean") {

6309                         // store className if set
6310                         data_priv.set(this, "__className__", this.className);
6311                     }

6314                     // then remove the whole classname (if there was one, the above saved it).
6315                     // Otherwise bring back whatever was previously saved (if anything),
6316                     // falling back to the empty string if nothing was stored.
6317                     this.className = this.className || value === false ? "" : data_priv.get(this, "__className__") || "";
6318                 }
6319             });
6320         };

6428             ///     1: Get the current value of the first element in the set of matched elements.
6429             ///     &#10;    1.1 - val()
6430             ///     &#10;2: Set the value of each element in the set of matched elements.
6431             ///     &#10;    2.1 - val(value) 
6432             ///     &#10;    2.2 - val(function(index, value))
6433             /// </summary>
6434             /// <param name="value" type="">
6435             ///     A string of text or an array of strings corresponding to the value of each matched element to set as selected/checked.
6436             /// </param>
6437             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6438     
6439             var hooks, ret, isFunction,
6440     			elem = this[0];
6441     
6442             if (!arguments.length) {
6443                 if (elem) {
6444                     hooks = jQuery.valHooks[elem.type] || jQuery.valHooks[elem.nodeName.toLowerCase()];
6445     
6446                     if (hooks && "get" in hooks && (ret = hooks.get(elem, "value")) !== undefined) {
6447                         return ret;
6448                     }
6449     
6450                     ret = elem.value;
6451     
6452                     return typeof ret === "string" ?
6453     					// handle most common string cases
6454     					ret.replace(rreturn, "") :
6455     					// handle cases where value is null/undef or number
6456     					ret == null ? "" : ret;
6457                 }
6458     
6459                 return;
6460             }
6461     
6462             isFunction = jQuery.isFunction(value);
6463     
6464             return this.each(function (i) {
6465                 var val,
6466     				self = jQuery(this);
6467     
6468                 if (this.nodeType !== 1) {
6469                     return;
6470                 }
6471     
6472                 if (isFunction) {
6473                     val = value.call(this, i, self.val());
6474                 } else {
6475                     val = value;
6476                 }
6477     
6478                 // Treat null/undefined as ""; convert numbers to string
6479                 if (val == null) {
6480                     val = "";
6481                 } else if (typeof val === "number") {
6482                     val += "";
6483                 } else if (jQuery.isArray(val)) {
6484                     val = jQuery.map(val, function (value) {
6485                         return value == null ? "" : value + "";
6486                     });
6487                 }
6488     
6489                 hooks = jQuery.valHooks[this.type] || jQuery.valHooks[this.nodeName.toLowerCase()];
6490     
6491                 // If set returns undefined, fall back to normal setting
6492                 if (!hooks || !("set" in hooks) || hooks.set(this, val, "value") === undefined) {
6493                     this.value = val;
6494                 }
6495             });
6496         };
6497         jQuery.prototype.width = function (margin, value) {
6498             /// <summary>
6499             ///     1: Get the current computed width for the first element in the set of matched elements.
6500             ///     &#10;    1.1 - width()
6501             ///     &#10;2: Set the CSS width of each element in the set of matched elements.
6502             ///     &#10;    2.1 - width(value) 
6503             ///     &#10;    2.2 - width(function(index, width))
6504             /// </summary>
6505             /// <param name="margin" type="">
6506             ///     An integer representing the number of pixels, or an integer along with an optional unit of measure appended (as a string).
6507             /// </param>
6508             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6509     
6510             var chainable = arguments.length && (defaultExtra || typeof margin !== "boolean"),
6511                 extra = defaultExtra || (margin === true || value === true ? "margin" : "border");
6512     
6513             return jQuery.access(this, function (elem, type, value) {
6514                 var doc;
6515     
6516                 if (jQuery.isWindow(elem)) {
6517                     // As of 5/8/2012 this will yield incorrect results for Mobile Safari, but there
6518                     // isn't a whole lot we can do. See pull request at this URL for discussion:
6519                     // https://github.com/jquery/jquery/pull/764
6520                     return elem.document.documentElement["client" + name];
6521                 }
6522     
6523                 // Get document width or height
6524                 if (elem.nodeType === 9) {
6525                     doc = elem.documentElement;
6526     
6527                     // Either scroll[Width/Height] or offset[Width/Height] or client[Width/Height],
6528                     // whichever is greatest
6529                     return Math.max(
6530                         elem.body["scroll" + name], doc["scroll" + name],
6531                         elem.body["offset" + name], doc["offset" + name],
6532                         doc["client" + name]
6533                     );
6534                 }
6535     
6536                 return value === undefined ?
6537                     // Get width or height on the element, requesting but not forcing parseFloat
6538                     jQuery.css(elem, type, extra) :
6539     
6540                     // Set width or height on the element
6541                     jQuery.style(elem, type, value, extra);
6542             }, type, chainable ? margin : undefined, chainable, null);
6543         };
6544         jQuery.prototype.wrap = function (html) {
6545             /// <summary>
6546             ///     Wrap an HTML structure around each element in the set of matched elements.
6547             ///     &#10;1 - wrap(wrappingElement) 
6548             ///     &#10;2 - wrap(function(index))
6549             /// </summary>
6550             /// <param name="html" type="">
6551             ///     A selector, element, HTML string, or jQuery object specifying the structure to wrap around the matched elements.
6552             /// </param>
6553             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6554     
6555             var isFunction = jQuery.isFunction(html);
6556     
6557             return this.each(function (i) {
6558                 jQuery(this).wrapAll(isFunction ? html.call(this, i) : html);
6559             });
6560         };
6561         jQuery.prototype.wrapAll = function (html) {
6562             /// <summary>
6563             ///     Wrap an HTML structure around all elements in the set of matched elements.
6564             /// </summary>
6565             /// <param name="html" type="">
6566             ///     A selector, element, HTML string, or jQuery object specifying the structure to wrap around the matched elements.
6567             /// </param>
6568             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6569     
6570             var wrap;
6571     
6572             if (jQuery.isFunction(html)) {
6573                 return this.each(function (i) {
6574                     jQuery(this).wrapAll(html.call(this, i));
6575                 });
6576             }
6577     
6578             if (this[0]) {
6579     
6580                 // The elements to wrap the target around
6581                 wrap = jQuery(html, this[0].ownerDocument).eq(0).clone(true);
6582     
6583                 if (this[0].parentNode) {
6584                     wrap.insertBefore(this[0]);
6585                 }
6586     
6587                 wrap.map(function () {
6588                     var elem = this;
6589     
6590                     while (elem.firstElementChild) {
6591                         elem = elem.firstElementChild;
6592                     }
6593     
6594                     return elem;
6595                 }).append(this);
6596             }
6597     
6598             return this;
6599         };
6600         jQuery.prototype.wrapInner = function (html) {
6601             /// <summary>
6602             ///     Wrap an HTML structure around the content of each element in the set of matched elements.
6603             ///     &#10;1 - wrapInner(wrappingElement) 
6604             ///     &#10;2 - wrapInner(function(index))
6605             /// </summary>
6606             /// <param name="html" type="String">
6607             ///     An HTML snippet, selector expression, jQuery object, or DOM element specifying the structure to wrap around the content of the matched elements.
6608             /// </param>
6609             /// <returns type="jQuery" />
6610     
6611             if (jQuery.isFunction(html)) {
6612                 return this.each(function (i) {
6613                     jQuery(this).wrapInner(html.call(this, i));
6614                 });
6615             }
6616     
6617             return this.each(function () {
6618                 var self = jQuery(this),
6619     				contents = self.contents();
6620     
6621                 if (contents.length) {
6622                     contents.wrapAll(html);
6623     
6624                 } else {
6625                     self.append(html);
6626                 }
6627             });
6628         };
6629         jQuery.fn = jQuery.prototype;
6630         jQuery.fn.init.prototype = jQuery.fn;
6631         window.jQuery = window.$ = jQuery;
6632     })(window);
